rComments: Great prof to have for FLS! She makes an effort to ensure everyone is understanding what's going on, and the worksheets are surprisingly helpful. Ironically, this class gave more homework than the class it accompanied, but overall well worth it. Marks are fair and will most likely boost your GPA. (Also, she's always smiling, which is nice.)

Mme Senneville is by far one of the best Profs I've ever had. I took her class as an accompanying class to my anthro lecture. Her class will bring your GPA up and the assignments are easy. She gives great feedback and marks quickly. Exams are open book as well and she's very lenient with assignments and extensions. Definitely recommend, every time.

She was a very good prof. for grammaire she is the best. And she always has a smile.  I actually enjoyed going to class.  She gave extra marks if you corrected your mistakes. The 2 books were very expensive... didn't really use them.  Buy used or share if you can.

This course pleasantly surprised me. I learned so much and it wasn't even that boring (as could possibly be expected with grammar). This prof is stellar. I had to take this course as part of my program but I would recommend it even as an elective.

Excellent teacher. One of the best I've had in FLS ever. She knows exactly what she's teaching and teaches it well. I learned the most in this class out of all of them (even more than 3771!) Definitely recommend a class with her if you have the chance. So nice and caring too!

Very useful course - learned a number of things about French that I should have been taught earlier. Would have been nice to have worked more on verbs in class, though. Fun, VERY nice lady - cares for her students and is always pleased to help.
